NAEP 2011 (http://nces.ed.gov/nationsreportcard/) is a cross-sectional survey that assesses what America's students know and can do in various subject areas. The study was conducted using computer-based assessments of students. Students in grades 4, 8, and 12 were sampled. NAEP 2011 assessments consist of national and state assessments in mathematics, reading, and writing. The study\ufffd\ufffd\ufffds response rates were between 87 and 98 percent. Key statistics produced from NAEP 2011 are results on subject-matter achievement, instructional experiences, and school environment for populations of students (e.g., all fourth-graders) and groups within those populations (e.g. female students, Hispanic students).</dct:description>         <dcat:keyword>assessment</dcat:keyword>         <dcat:keyword>math</dcat:keyword>
